def agent_action(execution_engine, member_id):
    me = execution_engine.current_members[member_id]
    relationships = execution_engine.relationship_dict
    victims = relationships['victim'][me.id]
    benefits = relationships['benefit'][me.id]
    benefit_land = relationships['benefit_land'][me.id]

    # Calculate total attacks against me
    total_attacks = victims.sum()

    # Identify top attackers
    attacker_ids = [i for i, val in enumerate(victims) if val > 0]
    attacker_strength = {i: victims[i] for i in attacker_ids}
    sorted_attackers = sorted(attacker_strength.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)

    # Identify allies based on benefits received
    ally_ids = [i for i, val in enumerate(benefits) if val > 60]

    # Decision making
    if me.vitality < 50.0 and ally_ids:
        # Seek help from strongest ally
        strongest_ally = ally_ids[0]
        execution_engine.offer(me, execution_engine.current_members[strongest_ally], True)
    elif total_attacks > 100:
        # Attack the top attacker
        top_attacker = sorted_attackers[0][0]
        execution_engine.attack(me, execution_engine.current_members[top_attacker])
    elif me.cargo < 30.0:
        # Bear resources from a less attacked member
        potential_members = [i for i in range(len(execution_engine.current_members)) if i != me.id and victims[i] < 20]
        if potential_members:
            target = potential_members[0]
            execution_engine.bear(me, execution_engine.current_members[target])
    else:
        # Strengthen alliances by offering benefits to top allies
        for ally in ally_ids:
            execution_engine.offer(me, execution_engine.current_members[ally], True)

def agent_action(execution_engine, member_id):
    me = execution_engine.current_members[member_id]
    # Analyze who has attacked me
    victim_matrix = execution_engine.relationship_dict['victim']
    attacks_received = victim_matrix[:, me.id]
    total_attacks = attacks_received.sum()

    # Identify the top attacker
    if attacks_received.size > 0:
        top_attacker_id = attacks_received.argmax()
        top_attacker = execution_engine.current_members[top_attacker_id]
    else:
        top_attacker = None

    # Analyze benefits received
    benefit_matrix = execution_engine.relationship_dict['benefit']
    benefits_received = benefit_matrix[:, me.id]
    top_benefactor_id = benefits_received.argmax()
    top_benefactor = execution_engine.current_members[top_benefactor_id]

    # Decision based on vitality
    if me.vitality < 40:
        # Offer help to top benefactor to strengthen alliance
        execution_engine.offer(me, top_benefactor, True)
    elif me.vitality < 70:
        if top_attacker and attacks_received[top_attacker.id] > 30:
            # Attack the most aggressive attacker
            execution_engine.attack(me, top_attacker)
        else:
            # Offer help to top benefactor
            execution_engine.offer(me, top_benefactor, True)
    else:
        # Maintain alliances or target weak attackers
        if top_attacker and attacks_received[top_attacker.id] > 20:
            execution_engine.attack(me, top_attacker)
        else:
            execution_engine.offer(me, top_benefactor, True)
